9.1 Critical Failure Modes

Failure Mode Probability Consequence Mitigation
SMES quench 10⁻⁴/launch Catastrophic Distributed coils, active protection
Track deformation 10⁻⁵/launch Major Redundant survey, active alignment
Sled derailment 10⁻⁶/launch Catastrophic Redundant guidance, emergency brakes
Power system fault 10⁻³/launch Minor Segmented architecture, bypass switches

9.2 Reliability Analysis

Using MIL-HDBK-217F models adapted for lunar environment:

Predicted Reliability:

· Mean Time Between Critical Failures (MTCF): 1,000 launches
· Availability: 0.95 (including maintenance)
· Single launch success probability: 0.9993

Redundancy Strategy: All critical systems have N+2 redundancy with independent failure modes.

